# RidgeRelay — Project Brief

This project is evaluated on design reasoning, safety tradeoffs, privacy considerations, and clarity of intent modeling—not on production readiness.

## Goal
Design a privacy-first safety platform concept that supports intent-aware monitoring, offline-first use, and predictable escalation for remote outdoor activity.

## Users
Hikers, trail runners, hunters, backcountry skiers/snowboarders, solo outdoor users.

## Key Constraints
- Low/no connectivity
- Battery limitations
- Privacy and consent requirements
- High cost of false alarms vs missed alerts

## Proposed Solution (High Level)
- Intent-based trip plan (route + timing + planned stops)
- Guardrails (corridor + stay/no-go zones)
- Intent-aware notifications
- Offline maps + probable service zones overlay
- Anonymous occupancy + opt-in crowd assist
- Staged escalation + emergency profile disclosure only on escalation

## What This Repo Contains
Static wireframe prototype (HTML/CSS/JS). No backend, GPS, or real dispatch integration.
 
## Success Criteria (Concept-Level)
- Reduces false alarms via intent modeling
- Preserves user privacy via session-limited permissions
- Makes escalation transparent and predictable
- Demonstrates realistic low-signal design considerations
